This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the compound MIMO wiretap channel. The paper discusses beamforming techniques and capacity calculations, which are common topics in the information theory sub-category (cs.IT). The paper also deals with security and eavesdropping, which falls under the computer security and cryptography sub-category (cs.CR). The use of computer simulations suggests that the paper may also fall under the multimedia sub-category (cs.MM) or the networking and internet architecture sub-category (cs.NI). Finally, the paper deals with optimization and control, which could place it in the systems and control sub-category (cs.SY).
